1
00:00:04,571 --> 00:00:05,903
<i>Previously on</i> ER:

2
00:00:06,073 --> 00:00:08,269
You should come to
my bible group sometime.

3
00:00:08,442 --> 00:00:10,274
Bible group? Okay.

4
00:00:10,444 --> 00:00:13,937
Do you think I wanna wait for you to
find out that he's jerking you around?

5
00:00:14,114 --> 00:00:17,050
You're making me think about
the way I want my life to be.

6
00:00:17,217 --> 00:00:18,879
This is Ben Parker.
He's the new RN.

7
00:00:19,052 --> 00:00:21,214
- Let me take you out to dinner.
- Like a date?

8
00:00:21,388 --> 00:00:23,584
We used to run into
homeless kids like this.

9
00:00:23,757 --> 00:00:27,194
- Please, just help Paulie.
- I can't. Paulie's very sick.

10
00:00:27,361 --> 00:00:28,954
I know your secret name. Mayday.

11
00:00:29,129 --> 00:00:31,530
And there's a crazy,
angry guy following us?

12
00:00:32,766 --> 00:00:34,064
Listen to me, Ames.

13
00:00:34,234 --> 00:00:36,931
Come near my family
again, I'll kill you.

14
00:00:47,948 --> 00:00:52,079
It was kind of fun until the chemo
kid called me Rudolph's skank.

15
00:00:52,252 --> 00:00:54,585
One of them asked me if
you were Sleepy or Sneezy.

16
00:00:54,755 --> 00:00:57,486
What? I'm an elf, I'm
not a freaking dwarf.

17
00:00:59,026 --> 00:01:01,655
- Oh, my God.
- Nice antlers.

18
00:01:01,828 --> 00:01:04,161
You guys look so cute.
I gotta get my camera.

19
00:01:04,331 --> 00:01:05,571
No, that's okay, really.

20
00:01:05,632 --> 00:01:06,930
- Was it fun at least?
- Yeah.

21
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,124
Pedes was a war zone.

22
00:01:08,302 --> 00:01:10,102
Heard you lost the pool, sorry.
- Yeah.

23
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:13,607
- That's one hot-looking dwarf you got.
- Know what? I'm an elf, damn it.

24
00:01:13,774 --> 00:01:15,436
Whoa. Oh, hey.

25
00:01:15,609 --> 00:01:17,441
As we commemorate
the birth of Jesus...

26
00:01:17,611 --> 00:01:20,513
I find myself contemplating
the vices I've been guilty of.

27
00:01:20,681 --> 00:01:23,310
And also the virtues...

28
00:01:23,483 --> 00:01:28,012
that I, that all of us born in sin and
striving for sanctity should aspire to.

29
00:01:28,188 --> 00:01:30,851
Turning our pride to humility.

30
00:01:31,024 --> 00:01:34,517
Our envy to compassion.

31
00:01:36,029 --> 00:01:39,363
Our anger to mercy.

32
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:43,995
Our laziness to activity.

33
00:01:44,871 --> 00:01:47,864
Our greed to generosity.

34
00:01:48,375 --> 00:01:52,710
Our gluttony to moderation.

35
00:01:54,381 --> 00:01:59,786
And last but not least, our
lust must be turned to...?

36
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,011
Archie?

37
00:02:03,924 --> 00:02:05,586
Um...

38
00:02:06,193 --> 00:02:07,718
Consummation?

39
00:02:11,198 --> 00:02:13,190
Yeah, no, no, seriously.

40
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:18,237
Our lust must be
turned to purity?

41
00:02:19,106 --> 00:02:24,067
Uh... Well, I was looking for
chastity, but talk about purity a little.

42
00:02:25,912 --> 00:02:31,010
Well, you know, I've always
taken it to mean purity of spirit...

43
00:02:31,184 --> 00:02:33,710
as opposed to a
literal, corporal purity.

44
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:36,219
Go on.

45
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:40,418
Uh... Well, you know, we
all live in the modern world.

46
00:02:40,594 --> 00:02:41,857
Right?

47
00:02:42,029 --> 00:02:45,431
And our virtuousness
shouldn't be locked...

48
00:02:45,599 --> 00:02:48,364
into some antiquated
notion of abstinence.

49
00:02:49,436 --> 00:02:50,904
Should it?

50
00:02:53,874 --> 00:02:56,105
- Shouldn't it?
- So...

51
00:02:56,610 --> 00:03:02,447
You're saying that you
can be sexually active...

52
00:03:02,616 --> 00:03:06,451
and still retain moral purity?

53
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:09,112
Not just me, sister, if
you know what I'm saying.

54
00:03:09,289 --> 00:03:10,757
Yes. Yeah.

55
00:03:10,924 --> 00:03:12,222
Look, well, no, no.

56
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:17,626
Because what I'm actually saying
is, at the end of the day, it's just...

57
00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:20,559
It's just us in the mirror...

58
00:03:20,967 --> 00:03:24,062
and we're the ones who
determine our own moral value.

59
00:03:25,172 --> 00:03:28,404
And to me, that's what
Christmas is all about.

60
00:03:31,978 --> 00:03:34,880
So you're not mad at me anymore?

61
00:03:36,183 --> 00:03:39,745
This is the first time in a
week I've seen you smile.

62
00:03:40,821 --> 00:03:44,155
Well, the holiday spirit is just so
infectious, I couldn't help myself...

63
00:03:44,324 --> 00:03:47,158
and I was waiting
for you to lighten up.

64
00:03:47,761 --> 00:03:49,161
Really?

65
00:03:49,329 --> 00:03:51,321
I was waiting for you.

66
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,599
Don't try to be charming
in that ridiculous outfit.

67
00:03:55,769 --> 00:03:58,136
Who, me? Charming?

68
00:04:01,975 --> 00:04:02,999
Back off, Rudolph.

69
00:04:03,176 --> 00:04:06,010
- Be nice.
- You be nice.

70
00:04:07,514 --> 00:04:09,540
Or you're not gonna
get your special present.

71
00:04:09,716 --> 00:04:11,514
What kind of present?

72
00:04:12,719 --> 00:04:14,017
A slightly naughty one.

73
00:04:14,187 --> 00:04:16,315
My favorite kind.

74
00:04:17,691 --> 00:04:19,125
Dr. Kovac?

75
00:04:19,292 --> 00:04:20,351
Sorry. You got a minute?

76
00:04:20,527 --> 00:04:22,018
Yeah, sure. Sure, yeah.

77
00:04:22,195 --> 00:04:23,629
It's about Curtis Ames.

78
00:04:23,797 --> 00:04:26,289
He's filed an order of
protection against you.

79
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:29,635
- A restraining order.
- That's ridiculous.

80
00:04:29,803 --> 00:04:31,897
Yeah, the judge who
issued it doesn't think so.

81
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:35,133
- The guy says you threatened to kill him.
- What?

82
00:04:35,308 --> 00:04:40,042
Look, you should've let it go, doc.
Now you look like the crazy one.

83
00:04:53,927 --> 00:04:55,190
Rufus Taylor, 35.

84
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:58,127
Going 60 on Dan Ryan,
crashed into an embankment.

85
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,494
Icicle shattered the
windshield, I couldn't see.

86
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:01,760
Icicle, huh?

87
00:05:01,935 --> 00:05:03,836
Came out of nowhere.
It was really big.

88
00:05:04,004 --> 00:05:06,030
- Anything hurt, man?
- My stomach.

89
00:05:06,239 --> 00:05:08,799
Trauma 1, let's go. Gates,
what's the RTS on this guy?

90
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:10,876
- The what?
- RTS. Revised Trauma Score.

91
00:05:11,044 --> 00:05:13,707
It correlates better than
GCS for traumatic brain injury.

92
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:15,712
- Traumatic brain what?
- You'll be fine, sir.

93
00:05:15,882 --> 00:05:17,009
What's the matter with you?

94
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:20,052
My shift was over. I couldn't
leave because you weren't here.

95
00:05:20,253 --> 00:05:23,052
Five minutes late. All right,
10 minutes. I'm here, now go.

96
00:05:23,256 --> 00:05:25,885
You have remedial command
of basics. I can't leave you.

97
00:05:26,059 --> 00:05:28,893
I would love to, believe me,
but it wouldn't be right, all right?

98
00:05:38,772 --> 00:05:41,503
Yeah. What are they gonna
say about it now, right?

99
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:43,644
Hey, merry Christmas, Neela.

100
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:45,403
- Where have you been?
- On the floor.

101
00:05:45,579 --> 00:05:47,548
- I thought we were rounding.
- What? No.

102
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:50,183
The Surgery Christmas
Party is the one time of year...

103
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:52,581
when we can forget
about disease and death...

104
00:05:52,786 --> 00:05:54,914
and celebrate
goodness, kindness.

105
00:05:55,288 --> 00:05:59,316
I admit I would prefer black
tie, sashimi and Veuve Clicquot...

106
00:05:59,492 --> 00:06:01,085
but still, it's Christmas.

107
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:02,421
I love it.

108
00:06:05,565 --> 00:06:07,193
- Yeah.
- Are you all right?

109
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,666
Sorry, it's gotta be this punch.

110
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:12,772
There's nothing even remotely
alcoholic in the punch, Dustin.

111
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:15,602
Right. Okay. Gotta go.

112
00:06:15,942 --> 00:06:17,911
Neela, I want you to
meet Manish Mehta.

113
00:06:18,078 --> 00:06:20,741
- He's gonna be helping us around here.
- Hi.

114
00:06:20,914 --> 00:06:23,349
Can I get everybody's
attention for a second, please?

115
00:06:23,516 --> 00:06:25,678
Everybody, listen up for a sec.

116
00:06:25,852 --> 00:06:27,115
Thanks.

117
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:31,257
Listen, it's fitting and
appropriate at this time of charity...

118
00:06:31,424 --> 00:06:33,950
and compassion for me
to be able to announce...

119
00:06:34,127 --> 00:06:37,393
the opening of Chicago's
only paired exchange program.

120
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,260
Yeah.

121
00:06:39,432 --> 00:06:41,196
And as an additional
Yuletide treat...

122
00:06:41,368 --> 00:06:44,532
we will be doing our
first kidney swap today.

123
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:49,339
Why don't we all get back to work
before we crash from the sugar high?

124
00:06:50,277 --> 00:06:51,540
- Nice to meet you.
- You too.

125
00:06:51,711 --> 00:06:54,203
Neela. Hi.

126
00:06:54,381 --> 00:06:56,316
Rob, you guys know
each other, right?

127
00:06:56,483 --> 00:06:58,975
Neela Rasgotra, I've
heard a lot about you.

128
00:06:59,152 --> 00:07:01,087
- You have?
- You're the golden girl...

129
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:04,850
Dubenko created a special
residency spot for. That's memorable.

130
00:07:05,392 --> 00:07:07,156
God, you must
really be something.

131
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,995
Okay, then. It's nice
to meet you, Rob.

132
00:07:10,163 --> 00:07:12,098
No, the pleasure's all mine.

133
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:16,426
Would you excuse me a minute?

134
00:07:23,677 --> 00:07:26,647
- You went to where Ames works?
- The police wouldn't do anything.

135
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:29,977
And you threatened to kill him,
and I'm the one who overreacted?

136
00:07:30,150 --> 00:07:32,847
- You think I made this up?
- I think you got carried away.

137
00:07:33,019 --> 00:07:34,817
I went to his work to
stop and scare him.

138
00:07:34,988 --> 00:07:36,115
Mission accomplished.

139
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:38,849
He's scared. He can have
you arrested if you get near him.

140
00:07:39,025 --> 00:07:41,620
Look, I didn't know
what else to do, okay?

141
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:43,855
I did it because I love
you, and I love Joe...

142
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:47,125
and I wasn't gonna let that
asshole keep threatening us, okay?

143
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,364
So it wasn't too geeky, was it?

144
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:55,475
Geeky? Lord, no. Or God, no.

145
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:58,476
I mean, no. No, I
enjoyed your Bible group.

146
00:07:58,645 --> 00:08:00,045
They were impressed by you.

147
00:08:00,213 --> 00:08:02,682
Yeah, what you said
was really advanced.

148
00:08:02,849 --> 00:08:04,442
- Really? You think?
- Yeah, I do.

149
00:08:04,617 --> 00:08:06,882
Oh, doughnuts. Ha-ha!

150
00:08:07,053 --> 00:08:09,420
The perks of authority.

151
00:08:10,056 --> 00:08:13,049
No, no, no. What
does this look like?

152
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,722
- Gluttony?
- Gluttony, exactly.

153
00:08:15,929 --> 00:08:18,990
I was just testing you. I'm
gonna save these for the kids.

154
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:22,067
Lenore Simkins, found down on
the street on 18th and Aberdeen.

155
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:24,727
Pulse ox is 91, looks like
frostbite on the fingertips.

156
00:08:24,938 --> 00:08:27,407
- Cold out there.
- Hi, Lenore. I'm Dr. Morris.

157
00:08:27,574 --> 00:08:30,339
I'd wish you merry Christmas
but as an employee of County...

158
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,412
I'm duty-bound to respect the
separation of church and state.

159
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:35,242
Are you kidding?

160
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:37,440
- Is he kidding?
- I think so.

161
00:08:41,087 --> 00:08:43,079
- Hey.
- Hey.

162
00:08:43,256 --> 00:08:45,088
- Got plans tonight?
- Yeah.

163
00:08:45,258 --> 00:08:48,057
Yeah, me too. With Ray.

164
00:08:48,228 --> 00:08:49,526
That's cool, right?

165
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,927
- It's none of my business.
- Okay.

166
00:08:52,098 --> 00:08:54,567
I just wanted to be sure.

167
00:08:55,769 --> 00:08:57,738
You look annoyed.

168
00:08:57,904 --> 00:09:01,272
Well, your friend from Vascular
went in almost 10 minutes ago.

169
00:09:01,474 --> 00:09:03,909
Yeah, I could tell you kind
of aggravated his problem.

170
00:09:04,077 --> 00:09:05,272
What problem?

171
00:09:05,478 --> 00:09:08,175
Rob's got a little
auto-stimulation issue.

172
00:09:09,249 --> 00:09:13,345
You know, he can't help tickling
the Elmo, spanking his monkey.

173
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:16,288
- It's how he got his nickname.
- What nickname?

174
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,885
We call him McCreamy.

175
00:09:19,793 --> 00:09:21,193
McCreamy?

176
00:09:26,132 --> 00:09:27,725
Hey, guys. Sorry about the wait.

177
00:09:28,201 --> 00:09:29,294
It's okay.

178
00:09:29,502 --> 00:09:32,233
God, it was great to
finally meet you, Neela.

179
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:34,931
I hope we get to
work together soon.

180
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:37,303
I gotta go.

181
00:09:39,512 --> 00:09:42,209
- How's that, Lenore? Better?
- Mm-hm.

182
00:09:44,617 --> 00:09:46,313
What are you doing
for the holidays?

183
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:49,580
Besides taking my kid to go
see <i>Return of the Evil Zombies?</i>

184
00:09:50,156 --> 00:09:53,149
Maybe before you go home,
you can let me buy you that drink?

185
00:09:53,526 --> 00:09:56,086
I don't know. I got
presents to wrap.

186
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:04,037
- Lenore, were you recently hospitalized?
- I was at City of Mercy till last night.

187
00:10:04,971 --> 00:10:07,463
- What for?
- Chest cold.

188
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,108
Winter's been hard.

189
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:11,141
How long were you there?

190
00:10:13,046 --> 00:10:16,039
Few days? I'm
not good with time.

191
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:18,045
Did they release you?

192
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:22,955
The lady at the hospital said the
ambulance was gonna take me back.

193
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:25,854
- Back home?
- Don't got one.

194
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:27,789
I make my own way.

195
00:10:28,561 --> 00:10:29,859
Where'd they drop you off?

196
00:10:30,563 --> 00:10:33,692
They left me in an
alley near 18th Street.

197
00:10:36,069 --> 00:10:39,335
I haven't slept in that
neighborhood in years.

198
00:10:39,939 --> 00:10:41,202
Second unit's infusing now?

199
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:44,037
I need sterile 10s and a
cordis. He needs central access.

200
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:47,476
- This is not good. I'll handle this.
- I know how to put in a line, Ray.

201
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:50,981
Mr. Taylor, we need to do an operation
to stop bleeding in your abdomen.

202
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:54,349
- Is there someone you want to be here?
- No. You sure this can't wait?

203
00:10:54,521 --> 00:10:56,319
I don't really want
this. Not today.

204
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:57,718
It's okay, you'll be fine.

205
00:10:57,891 --> 00:11:00,190
It's just, my karma's
not so good right now.

206
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,226
It's not the best time
to go under the knife.

207
00:11:02,395 --> 00:11:03,454
Don't worry, sir.

208
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:06,122
Here, we treat the naughty as
well as the nice all year round.

209
00:11:06,299 --> 00:11:08,063
We'll take good care of you.

210
00:11:08,234 --> 00:11:10,362
I promise this
is the best thing.

211
00:11:10,537 --> 00:11:11,561
Mayday.

212
00:11:11,738 --> 00:11:14,173
O.R. 2. Dubenko
should be waiting.

213
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:16,104
Mayday.

214
00:11:17,243 --> 00:11:19,235
Go on, I'll be right up.

215
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,510
- Lizzie's sick.
- We were worried about you.

216
00:11:27,687 --> 00:11:29,315
Lizzie's sick. You need to come.

217
00:11:29,489 --> 00:11:31,754
Your friend? Does she
have what Paulie had?

218
00:11:31,925 --> 00:11:34,417
I don't know. You need to come.

219
00:11:36,129 --> 00:11:38,860
- All right, wait there.
- Pick up the old chart from Records.

220
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:41,501
- Get the echo from CICU.
- What about the toilet bowls?

221
00:11:41,668 --> 00:11:44,103
- I haven't scrubbed them yet.
- Come with me a minute?

222
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:46,535
- Oh, thank God.
- Where do you think you're going?

223
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:49,574
Do you have a toenail extraction
you want me to take notes on?

224
00:11:49,742 --> 00:11:53,008
- Are you too advanced for this?
- If we have problem, spit it out.

225
00:11:53,179 --> 00:11:56,240
- I don't speak bitchy.
- Oh, you seem pretty fluent to me.

226
00:11:56,416 --> 00:12:00,285
- Get somebody else, my intern's busy.
- Stop being an idiot, I need Tony's help.

227
00:12:01,154 --> 00:12:02,713
And you too, I've had enough.

228
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:04,721
Why don't you either
slap each other silly...

229
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:06,553
or kiss now and
get it over with?

230
00:12:11,364 --> 00:12:13,390
She got bad last night.
Pains everywhere.

231
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:15,159
Tell me where, I'll
send an ambulance.

232
00:12:15,335 --> 00:12:17,497
- No. I'll take you.
- Doesn't work like that.

233
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:20,196
Please. You helped Paulie.

234
00:12:20,373 --> 00:12:21,705
You heard about Paulie?

235
00:12:21,874 --> 00:12:23,502
I came back a few days after.

236
00:12:23,676 --> 00:12:26,202
The man at the desk said
he was at the care unit.

237
00:12:26,379 --> 00:12:28,075
That's good, right?

238
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:29,272
Come on.

239
00:12:29,449 --> 00:12:31,247
If she's sick, she
needs to be in hospital.

