- Is that what you call lying?

483
00:24:45,718 --> 00:24:47,619
I wasn't gonna take a
chance on losing them.

484
00:24:47,786 --> 00:24:49,482
You turned us into
every bad adult...

485
00:24:49,655 --> 00:24:53,057
- that these kids were ever screwed by.
- That's so sweet and so naive.

486
00:24:53,225 --> 00:24:55,057
I'll send a van to pick
up the other children.

487
00:24:55,227 --> 00:24:57,059
- Good.
- If you pick them up today...

488
00:24:57,229 --> 00:24:58,390
they'll be gone tomorrow.

489
00:24:58,564 --> 00:25:00,055
These kids won't just submit.

490
00:25:00,232 --> 00:25:02,895
Need to be convinced that
they'll be safe and protected.

491
00:25:03,068 --> 00:25:04,559
We'll try to keep them together.

492
00:25:04,737 --> 00:25:06,899
I can't promise they
won't end up in foster care.

493
00:25:07,072 --> 00:25:10,065
- But you'll make sure they're okay, right?
- We always do.

494
00:25:10,242 --> 00:25:13,474
Come on. These kids are smart.
They know that that's not how it goes.

495
00:25:13,645 --> 00:25:16,205
A social worker will follow
up. It's the best I can do.

496
00:25:16,382 --> 00:25:18,749
No, no, no. That's
not good enough.

497
00:25:20,152 --> 00:25:22,212
I can't believe you got
CPS to agree to that.

498
00:25:22,388 --> 00:25:24,050
Actually, it was
Ray's brainstorm.

499
00:25:24,223 --> 00:25:27,352
The trick's getting
the kids to accept it.

500
00:25:27,826 --> 00:25:29,089
Teller. Listen.

501
00:25:29,495 --> 00:25:31,589
Child Protective Services...

502
00:25:31,764 --> 00:25:34,859
has arranged for all of you to
live together in a group home.

503
00:25:35,034 --> 00:25:37,526
- You said no foster care.
- Hear us out, Teller...

504
00:25:38,270 --> 00:25:41,365
- Wait, Teller, Teller.
- No, I won't go. You lied!

505
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,941
It's not safe out
there, all right?

506
00:25:44,109 --> 00:25:46,874
We survive. No one hurts us.

507
00:25:47,046 --> 00:25:49,515
What Lizzie's doing, having
sex for money and shelter?

508
00:25:49,681 --> 00:25:52,412
- That's hurting her. Hurting all of you.
- Don't say that!

509
00:25:52,584 --> 00:25:55,019
If you weren't sleeping in
old abandoned buildings...

510
00:25:55,187 --> 00:25:57,418
Paulie would have
never gotten sick.

511
00:25:57,589 --> 00:25:59,490
But you fixed him.

512
00:25:59,925 --> 00:26:00,984
He's getting better.

513
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:04,287
No, we didn't.

514
00:26:04,496 --> 00:26:06,488
Paulie died.

515
00:26:13,305 --> 00:26:15,797
I'm sorry. I wanted
to tell you his...

516
00:26:17,009 --> 00:26:20,309
His infection was too severe
and we couldn't save him but...

517
00:26:20,512 --> 00:26:21,536
I wanna see him.

518
00:26:21,713 --> 00:26:23,909
I know I lied to you. I'm
not gonna lie anymore.

519
00:26:24,083 --> 00:26:25,415
I don't believe you.

520
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:28,110
It's not working. The way
you're living is not working.

521
00:26:28,287 --> 00:26:30,813
- You're a smart kid. You can see that.
- Let go, let go.

522
00:26:31,023 --> 00:26:34,653
Listen to me. You can't
go on like this anymore.

523
00:26:41,467 --> 00:26:42,833
Teller...

524
00:26:43,836 --> 00:26:45,532
Lizzie agreed to go.

525
00:26:47,039 --> 00:26:49,531
It's the only way she
can keep her baby.

526
00:26:52,111 --> 00:26:54,603
And the rest of us will
just stay with them?

527
00:26:55,547 --> 00:26:56,845
That's right.

528
00:26:57,049 --> 00:26:59,450
And Dr. Gates will come
and visit every two weeks...

529
00:26:59,618 --> 00:27:01,610
and make sure things
are okay, all right?

530
00:27:03,755 --> 00:27:07,123
You need me for anything at any
time, you call me, and I'll be there.

531
00:27:09,061 --> 00:27:10,324
You would do that?

532
00:27:11,330 --> 00:27:12,354
Yeah.

533
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:17,201
Listen.

534
00:27:18,103 --> 00:27:21,164
Now, I need you to take the social
workers to where the others are.

535
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:24,037
And let the kids know that
it's okay and safe to come in.

536
00:27:24,209 --> 00:27:25,939
Will you do that?

537
00:27:27,613 --> 00:27:29,878
I'll wait with you
here, Teller. Come on.

538
00:27:31,016 --> 00:27:32,575
Thank you.

539
00:27:33,352 --> 00:27:36,379
Well, that went better
than expected, huh?

540
00:27:36,588 --> 00:27:37,612
Yeah?

541
00:27:37,789 --> 00:27:40,281
That kid may not survive
another round of your games.

542
00:27:40,459 --> 00:27:42,826
Come on, I've been
trying to help the kid all day.

543
00:27:42,995 --> 00:27:44,987
Gates, you'll say
anything to seal the deal.

544
00:27:45,164 --> 00:27:48,066
I understand that. I've done that.
But these are messed-up kids.

545
00:27:48,233 --> 00:27:51,135
- You gotta draw the line somewhere.
- And what line is that?

546
00:27:52,804 --> 00:27:56,571
If you're making promises you
have no intention of keeping...

547
00:27:56,742 --> 00:27:58,335
just cut loose.

548
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:00,911
Minimize the damage, okay?

549
00:28:02,681 --> 00:28:04,616
This isn't just
about the kids, is it?

550
00:28:06,818 --> 00:28:08,719
No, it's not.

551
00:28:15,093 --> 00:28:20,396
Hey, how about you give me a
few hours to wrap some presents?

552
00:28:30,475 --> 00:28:33,673
- Can we talk?
- Sure.

553
00:28:36,014 --> 00:28:37,505
This scares me.

554
00:28:38,884 --> 00:28:40,819
What, Ames?

555
00:28:41,620 --> 00:28:43,179
What it's doing to you.

556
00:28:44,656 --> 00:28:45,680
To us.

557
00:28:49,795 --> 00:28:51,821
It took us so long to get here.

558
00:28:51,997 --> 00:28:53,795
All of us.

559
00:28:53,966 --> 00:28:56,993
And the way you're acting, how
it's taking over our whole lives...

560
00:28:57,169 --> 00:29:01,004
it makes me scared
we're gonna lose this.

561
00:29:11,283 --> 00:29:13,479
When Jasna and the kids died...

562
00:29:13,652 --> 00:29:18,056
I needed to make a change
and I decided to move here.

563
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:20,858
Made my brother really angry.

564
00:29:21,026 --> 00:29:22,221
He said...

565
00:29:22,427 --> 00:29:27,024
He said that I was a coward
and that I was running away.

566
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:34,196
And it's only recently that I've
come to know that he was wrong.

567
00:29:36,308 --> 00:29:38,971
I wasn't running
away from anything.

568
00:29:41,380 --> 00:29:43,372
I was running to you.

569
00:29:47,886 --> 00:29:51,323
And I'll never let
anything take this away.

570
00:30:13,345 --> 00:30:15,746
Did I mention how
hot you look in antlers?

571
00:30:24,423 --> 00:30:27,689
- I think she's in here, Santa.
- Ho, ho, ho!

572
00:30:27,859 --> 00:30:30,124
Has anyone seen a little
girl named Melia Simon?

573
00:30:30,295 --> 00:30:31,388
That's her right there.

574
00:30:31,563 --> 00:30:37,059
Oh, my reindeer needed a little rest,
so I thought I'd come by and say hi.

575
00:30:37,235 --> 00:30:38,726
How do you do? I'm Santa Claus.

576
00:30:38,904 --> 00:30:40,099
Hi, Santa.

577
00:30:40,272 --> 00:30:42,104
Can't stay long,
very, very busy.

578
00:30:42,274 --> 00:30:46,405
Gotta deliver presents to the
whole western hemisphere tonight.

579
00:30:46,778 --> 00:30:48,804
Nice try, Archie.
I know it's you.

580
00:30:50,048 --> 00:30:53,246
Archie? Who's Archie?

581
00:30:53,418 --> 00:30:57,048
I'm 9 years old. I know
there's no Santa, okay?

582
00:30:57,723 --> 00:30:59,885
You know, you're
a bright girl, Melia.

583
00:31:00,058 --> 00:31:01,526
But you're wrong about that.

584
00:31:02,094 --> 00:31:04,757
It's a fake beard
and a dumb suit.

585
00:31:05,330 --> 00:31:07,993
Don't you know
that there's a rule...

586
00:31:08,166 --> 00:31:11,659
that if millions of kids believe in
the same thing, it becomes real?

587
00:31:12,137 --> 00:31:13,901
- That's not a rule.
- Yeah.

588
00:31:14,072 --> 00:31:18,840
Every time you're generous or thoughtful
or help someone who needs help...

589
00:31:19,044 --> 00:31:21,411
that's a little
bit of Santa too.

590
00:31:22,180 --> 00:31:23,842
What are you talking about?

591
00:31:25,784 --> 00:31:27,252
Come on.

592
00:31:27,786 --> 00:31:31,188
Santa Claus represents one of
the last remaining bits of magic...

593
00:31:31,356 --> 00:31:32,654
left in this world.

594
00:31:32,824 --> 00:31:38,456
Now, I still believe, so
don't spoil it for me, okay?

595
00:31:39,765 --> 00:31:40,926
Come on.

596
00:31:41,099 --> 00:31:42,692
Where we going?

597
00:31:47,839 --> 00:31:49,637
Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho!

598
00:31:49,808 --> 00:31:51,174
Wait, it's Santa.

599
00:31:51,343 --> 00:31:54,836
Oh, you were a very,
very nice girl this year.

600
00:31:55,013 --> 00:31:56,641
Top of the nice list.

601
00:31:56,815 --> 00:31:59,808
Would it be all right
if I signed your cast?

602
00:32:00,886 --> 00:32:02,514
Thank you.

603
00:32:03,989 --> 00:32:06,618
To Greta...

604
00:32:06,892 --> 00:32:09,191
Keep on being nice.

605
00:32:09,361 --> 00:32:11,387
Love, Santa.

606
00:32:11,596 --> 00:32:13,064
How'd you know my name?

607
00:32:13,231 --> 00:32:15,564
Come on, I'm Santa Claus, huh?

608
00:32:15,734 --> 00:32:17,794
Merry Christmas.

609
00:32:18,904 --> 00:32:20,736
It's the real Santa, isn't it?

610
00:32:21,907 --> 00:32:23,034
Yeah.

611
00:32:23,208 --> 00:32:24,608
It is.

612
00:32:29,181 --> 00:32:31,582
You lost almost a third
of your blood volume.

613
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:35,209
Give us a few
days to buff you up.

614
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:39,714
Plus, I have a present for you.

615
00:32:40,358 --> 00:32:44,625
These are for them.

616
00:32:48,700 --> 00:32:52,034
Things were a little touch-and-go
for a while, so I called them.

617
00:32:52,771 --> 00:32:54,740
- How do I explain...?
- It's Christmas.

618
00:32:54,906 --> 00:32:57,171
You don't have to. Trust me.

619
00:33:00,178 --> 00:33:02,841
Hey, princess.

620
00:33:03,215 --> 00:33:04,342
Hey, buddy.

621
00:33:04,516 --> 00:33:06,747
Look at you guys.

622
00:33:07,452 --> 00:33:08,750
You're all grown up.

623
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,400
You getting out of here soon?

624
00:33:10,455 --> 00:33:13,857
I have a cajillion
notes to write.

625
00:33:14,025 --> 00:33:15,891
- You look nice.
- Thanks.

626
00:33:16,061 --> 00:33:18,758
- Off to your sister's, I take it?
- Yeah.

627
00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:22,094
It's for you. Merry
Christmas, Neela.

628
00:33:22,267 --> 00:33:23,428
I don't normally do this.

629
00:33:23,602 --> 00:33:26,868
Work presents always end up being
something edible and bad for you...

630
00:33:27,038 --> 00:33:29,439
or something impersonal
like organic soap.

631
00:33:29,608 --> 00:33:32,407
Who needs that crap cluttering
up their bathroom anyway?

632
00:33:32,577 --> 00:33:35,069
Oh, loops, wow.

633
00:33:35,247 --> 00:33:37,478
Yeah. That's my very first pair.

634
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:40,151
Bought them for
myself in med school.

635
00:33:40,318 --> 00:33:42,310
Thank you. It's a lovely gift.

636
00:33:44,456 --> 00:33:45,947
Listen.

637
00:33:47,626 --> 00:33:53,566
You're an intern and I'm an Attending,
and there are certain protocols...

638
00:33:53,732 --> 00:33:58,227
certain hierarchies
that preclude me from...

639
00:33:58,403 --> 00:33:59,427
Lucien.

640
00:33:59,604 --> 00:34:01,573
Being direct about
this, but it's Christmas...

641
00:34:01,740 --> 00:34:03,641
what the hell, I'm
just gonna say it.

642
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:09,213
You're a really
good surgeon, Neela.

643
00:34:11,816 --> 00:34:14,012
A few more years
and you could be great.

644
00:34:17,489 --> 00:34:19,082
Thank you.

645
00:34:21,226 --> 00:34:22,990
You're gonna try them on?

646
00:34:23,828 --> 00:34:25,319
I will.

647
00:34:31,770 --> 00:34:32,829
Beautiful.

648
00:34:33,338 --> 00:34:36,775
You repeat this conversation to
anyone, and I will deny it. You know that.

649
00:34:36,942 --> 00:34:38,376
What conversation?

650
00:34:38,543 --> 00:34:40,136
Lovely.

651
00:34:40,312 --> 00:34:41,712
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- Yeah.

652
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:44,281
Transplant rounds are at 7.

653
00:34:55,894 --> 00:34:58,762
Thank you. Bye, sweetheart.

654
00:35:04,769 --> 00:35:07,034
Look out, Kriss Kringle.
What's going on, Morris?

655
00:35:07,205 --> 00:35:08,969
Oh, we did okay, Greg.

656
00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:10,540
Just okay?

657
00:35:10,709 --> 00:35:13,372
Either you rocked the house
or you were closed to patients.

658
00:35:13,545 --> 00:35:15,377
No, we just moved
people through.

659
00:35:15,547 --> 00:35:18,039
All right, all right. Go
ahead, you can gloat now.

660
00:35:18,216 --> 00:35:20,378
Tell me all about what a
great manager you are.

661
00:35:20,552 --> 00:35:23,351
I saved Jerry, I diagnosed
D.I.D., yadda yadda.

662
00:35:23,521 --> 00:35:24,989
Know what?

663
00:35:26,091 --> 00:35:28,560
I'm gonna go with
humility this time.

664
00:35:29,094 --> 00:35:30,562
For real.

665
00:35:32,163 --> 00:35:33,187
Humili -what?

666
00:35:35,100 --> 00:35:36,432
Hey.

667
00:35:36,901 --> 00:35:39,393
I learned a lot
watching you today.

668
00:35:40,038 --> 00:35:42,405
Yeah, well, I'm
full of it, Hope.

669
00:35:42,907 --> 00:35:45,536
I get it, Archie.

670
00:35:45,710 --> 00:35:49,272
I know you don't believe
half of what you say but...

671
00:35:49,447 --> 00:35:51,075
You know what?

672
00:35:51,750 --> 00:35:53,309
It doesn't really matter.

673
00:35:54,085 --> 00:35:57,749
Because I saw you today.

674
00:35:57,922 --> 00:36:03,953
And what I saw was a
guy who's trying to be good.

675
00:36:04,129 --> 00:36:05,597
And...

676
00:36:06,131 --> 00:36:09,260
I don't know, that right
there is half the battle.

677
00:36:12,203 --> 00:36:14,138
Have a good holiday.

678
00:36:14,773 --> 00:36:15,832
What are you doing?

679
00:36:17,475 --> 00:36:18,534
What?

680
00:36:20,245 --> 00:36:23,579
Now. Are you going home?

681
00:36:23,748 --> 00:36:26,149
I thought maybe we could...

682
00:36:27,285 --> 00:36:30,449
Grab a bite, get a
drink, see what happens.

683
00:36:33,658 --> 00:36:36,719
Chastity's always
been overrated.

684
00:36:36,895 --> 00:36:41,924
Purity of spirit is what
it's all about, right?

685
00:36:43,868 --> 00:36:45,666
Wait, wait, are you...?

686
00:36:46,237 --> 00:36:47,432
What are you saying?

687
00:36:58,116 --> 00:36:59,641
You know what?

688
00:37:04,255 --> 00:37:05,587
I don't think so.

689
00:37:08,993 --> 00:37:10,393
What?

690
00:37:11,830 --> 00:37:15,926
I hate that I'm saying this.

691
00:37:16,801 --> 00:37:20,169
It's like some dorky angel
has taken control of my mouth.

692
00:37:20,805 --> 00:37:22,034
But...

693
00:37:22,941 --> 00:37:24,136
No.

694
00:37:26,277 --> 00:37:27,609
What?

695
00:37:29,013 --> 00:37:30,037
What?

696
00:37:30,215 --> 00:37:35,051
It's Christmas, and people
get lonely on Christmas...

697
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:37,712
and we might do something
that we'd both regret...

698
00:37:37,922 --> 00:37:42,417
or could get in the way of a possibly
deeper relationship in the future.

699
00:37:43,194 --> 00:37:44,719
So...

700
00:37:46,364 --> 00:37:48,799
I'm sorry.

701
00:37:51,536 --> 00:37:53,402
Hey. Hey.

702
00:37:53,571 --> 00:37:56,131
You stole my suit.

703
00:37:56,708 --> 00:37:58,700
Well, what about you?

704
00:37:59,344 --> 00:38:00,710
Me?

705
00:38:01,045 --> 00:38:02,570
Yes, where are you from...

706
00:38:02,747 --> 00:38:05,546
what are you doing
here, what's your damage?

707
00:38:06,451 --> 00:38:08,420
I spent a couple of
years in the service...

708
00:38:08,586 --> 00:38:10,680
and managed to spend
my time in Okinawa...

709
00:38:10,855 --> 00:38:14,223
which is a hell of a lot better
than being in Iraq or Afghanistan.

710
00:38:14,726 --> 00:38:16,854
Since I've come back,
I work as a traveler.

711
00:38:17,028 --> 00:38:19,725
Yeah, I did that for a while,
but then I got tired of it.

712
00:38:19,898 --> 00:38:22,527
So wait, you have
what, a week or so left?

713
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:24,328
It's supposed to be a week.

714
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:26,835
But this place seems all right.

715
00:38:27,005 --> 00:38:29,065
It seems like
pretty great people.

716
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:33,075
I mean, like, what we did for
that lady today, what you did...

717
00:38:33,378 --> 00:38:34,402
That was something.

718
00:38:34,579 --> 00:38:39,074
Come on, everyone deserves a
little bit of happiness at Christmastime.

719
00:38:39,784 --> 00:38:41,480
Yeah.

720
00:38:44,355 --> 00:38:47,484
So I called the nursing director,
and I signed on for another month.

721
00:38:48,593 --> 00:38:49,617
Really?

722
00:38:50,261 --> 00:38:51,729
Really.

723
00:38:56,768 --> 00:38:58,100
Well.

724
00:38:59,103 --> 00:39:00,731
Merry Christmas, Ben.

725
00:39:02,774 --> 00:39:04,606
Merry Christmas, Samantha.

726
00:41:49,807 --> 00:41:51,435
Idiot.

727
00:41:51,609 --> 00:41:53,441
Moron.

728
00:41:55,980 --> 00:41:57,448
She was right there.

729
00:41:57,615 --> 00:42:00,483
Right there for the fondling,
and you just let her go.

730
00:42:00,685 --> 00:42:02,119
Why? Why?

731
00:42:02,286 --> 00:42:05,688
Why'd you have to be
such a good Christian, huh?

732
00:42:06,290 --> 00:42:10,318
There's no God.
There's no Christmas.

733
00:42:10,895 --> 00:42:14,093
There's no freaking Santa Claus.

734
00:42:23,508 --> 00:42:26,706
Merry Christmas.

735
00:42:27,145 --> 00:42:28,807
Holy...
